snippet.title: What's The Sharpest homemade Katana?
snippet.description:
SUBSCRIBE & ADOPT A KATANA WITH THE LINK IN BIO!!

If you love katana unboxing, then you'll love this. See the Katanas slice in action as satisfying as ASMR! These aren't rusted katanas! Sword-making, blacksmithing, knife making, and katana making are Mini Katana's passions! Be like your favorite hero in Wild Heart, Blox fruit, or Elden ring, and test your slicing skill with a Karakuri Katana, Nodachi, cursed dual katana, moonveil katana build, rivers of blood katana, or the true triple katana. Forget how to make paper katanas or lego katanas these are real carbon steel! Subscribe to watch mini katana unboxing, how to make a katana with cardboard and with paper, and more!  The Mini Katana Store is committed to high quality carbon steel blades and giving you slice of life looks as we try not to laugh challenge. snippet.title: Diamond Platnumz feat Bien - Katam (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Get Katam👇👇👇
https://dplatnumz.lnk.to/katam

"KATAM" is a sweet, catchy love anthem that brings together two East African powerhouses—Diamond Platnumz and @BienOfficial in a celebration of beauty, love, and unity across the continent. The song produced by S2Kizzy is all about that one special woman who leaves you completely speechless—her vibe, her shape, her roots—everything about her is katam tam, meaning irresistibly sweet. Through playful lyrics and smooth harmonies, Diamond and Bien paint a picture of a woman whose charm reflects the richness of East Africa—from her Rwandan glow, Somali hair, Ethiopian eyes, to her Tanzanian sweetness and Kenyan smarts. It's flirty, fun, and full of pride—an Afro-pop jam that makes you want to dance, fall in love, and raise a toast to all the beautiful queens of Africa."

snippet.title: Mbosso - Pawa (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Music video by Mbosso performing, “Pawa” (Power), is a heartfelt, poetic love song by Mbosso that captures the overwhelming power of deep affection. Using rich metaphors and smooth vocals, he likens love to an intoxicating force that leaves him weak and emotionally charged — “naishiwa pawa” (I’m losing power). The lyrics blend vulnerability with admiration, painting his lover as a source of strength and inspiration. With a melodic blend of Bongo Flava and soulful instrumentation, “Pawa” showcases Mbosso’s lyrical depth and emotive style. The music was shot in Iringa, Tanzania, Directed by Folex & Audio produced by S2Kizzy.

snippet.title: Kenya Protest LIVE: Police Block Roads To Nairobi on Anniversary of Pro-Democracy Protests | N18G
snippet.description:
Kenya Protest LIVE: Protests in Nairobi, Kenya on Anniversary of Historic Pro-Democracy March | CNBC TV18
Nairobi, Kenya - Protests expected in Kenya on anniversary of historic pro-democracy march. Known as Saba Saba (Seven Seven), July 7 is remembered as the day Kenyans took to the streets in 1990 demanding multi-party democracy. This year, the anniversary is set against a backdrop of rising public anger over police brutality, abductions of activists, corruption, and a deepening economic crisis. Protesters are expected to gather in the Central Business District, with a strong police presence anticipated.
Kenyans hold a protest in Nairobi against police brutality, as anger has reignited over the longstanding issue by the death of blogger Albert Ojwang in police custody and the close-range shooting by police of vendor Boniface Kariuki during protests for Ojwang mid-June. Human rights groups have long called for action over illegal arrests, detentions and torture of government critics in Kenya. President William Ruto has vowed to end police brutality and said no enforced disappearances would happen during his administration. But Ruto's interior minister told police to “shoot on sight” anyone who approaches police stations during protests, after five police stations were torched.
